<exploration xml:id="warm-actuemoslo-otraManera" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>Actuémoslo: Otra manera</title>

<statement>
  <p><image source="png-source/3 ducks.png" width="60%">
    <shortdescription>(Encontremos grupos que tengan el mismo número de cosas)</shortdescription>
    </image>
  </p>
  <p>
    <line>3 patitos muy lejos de aquí</line> 
    <line>a la colina salieron a pasear.</line>
    <line>Mamá pata dijo: “Cuac, cuac, cuac.”</line>
    <line>Después 3 patitos vio regresar.</line>
  </p>
</statement>

<solution>
  <p>[++++++++++++]</p>
  
  <p>Sample responses:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Three kids could pretend to be ducks.</li>
    <li>We could draw 3 ducks.</li>
    <li>We could show the 3 ducks on our fingers.</li>
  </ul>
</solution>


<!-- ============================================================== 
   Notas profesor <prelude> (se pueden mostrar previo al enunciado)                      
===================================================================  -->
<prelude component="profesor"> 

  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="recommended-time-titulo"/></title>
    <p>10 minutos</p>
  </paragraphs>

  
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this activity is for students to consider different ways of acting out a story. Students revisit the story from previous lessons. They suggest different ways the story could be acted out. Acting out gives students opportunities to make sense of a context (MP1). In the synthesis, the class acts out the story with either concrete objects or drawings, whichever was not done in the previous lesson.</p>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="materials-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[@@@@@@@@@]</p>
  </paragraphs> -->


  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="launch-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Groups of 2</li>
      <li>Display and read the story.</li>
      <li><q>¿De qué se trata la historia?</q></li>
      <li>30 seconds: quiet think time</li>
      <li>Share responses.</li>
      <li>Read the story again.</li>
      <li><q>¿Cómo pueden actuar esta historia?</q></li>
      <li>30 seconds: quiet think time</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>


  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="instructions-teacher-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li><q>Discutan con su pareja cómo pensaron</q></li>
      <li>1 minute: partner discussion</li>
      <li>Monitor for students who suggest using physical objects such as fingers, cubes or students to represent the story, or drawing pictures to represent the story.</li>
      <li>Share responses.</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

</prelude>

<!-- ============================================================== 
   Notas profesor <postlude> (se pueden mostrar después del enunciado)                      
===================================================================  -->
<postlude component="profesor">

  <!-- <paragraphs>
